<h1 class="bac"><%=program.Item("title")%></h1>

<div class="expanded">
<% call expandableH2("our_business", true) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America is one of the world&#39;s largest financial institutions, serving individual consumers, small- and middle-market businesses and large corporations with a full range of banking, investing, asset management and other financial and risk management products and services. The company provides unmatched convenience in the United States, serving approximately 57 million consumer and small business relationships with approximately 5,900 retail banking offices and approximately 18,000 ATMs and award-winning online banking with 29 million active users.</p>
<h3 class="bac">Consumer and Small Business Banking MBA Intern Program</h3>
<p class="bac">Internship program designed to prepare future MBA graduates for the full time Consumer and Small Business Bank MBA Program.</p>
<p class="bac">The Consumer  &amp; Small Business Banking MBA Program develops future leaders while engaging them in challenging and business critical assignments in both client facing and non-client facing roles. Within the full time program recent MBA level graduates experience a 2 year rotational program rotating through 3 areas of the CSBB organization. These areas are: Retail Banking, Preferred and Small Business Banking, Consumer Banking Products and CSBB Distribution.</p>
<p class="bac">The internship program mirrors the full time program supporting each of these businesses. During the 10 week internship, candidates will engage in a challenging assignment within one of these businesses working on a variety of assignments. The internship is meant to provide us an opportunity to evaluate candidates for the full time program while simultaneously providing the intern some insight into our organization.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Our 10 week assignments may include any of the following areas:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Product Design</li>
	<li>Product Management</li>
	<li>Strategy Development</li>
	<li>Business Support</li>
	<li>Channel Integration</li>
	<li>Analytics</li>
	<li>Relationship Management</li>
	<li>Coaching and Development</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("qualifications", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Ideal candidate will exhibit a strong drive for results; succeed in a fast-paced, empowered, and collaborative environment; enjoy teamwork and partnering with others; possess financial acumen, excellent organizational and strong analytical skills; strong technical skills and ability to build/design and execute strategy. The ability to learn the organizational structure, the formal/informal workings of the organization and to convey a strong sense of customer and associate satisfaction to drive shareholder value is required.</p>
<p class="bac nobr">Additional requirements include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Must be an MBA candidate at an accredited university during the time of the internship</li>
	<li>Must be a first year MBA student</li>
	<li>Spring/Summer 2013 graduation date.</li>
	<li>4-7 years pre-M.B.A. work experience with a demonstrated record of achievement. .</li>
	<li>Relevant work history that reflects experience in supervising others, delegating tasks and resolving conflicts.</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility/flexibility</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac nobr">Preferred Expertise and/or experience in at least 3 of the following:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to navigate in a highly matrixed environment</li>
	<li>Ability to influence</li>
	<li>Experience in execution/production for end to end processes</li>
	<li>Previous financial services or retail management experience</li>
	<li>Strong statistical/analytical background (familiarity with Six Sigma principles)</li>
	<li>Team/project management experience</li>
	<li>Strategy and/or business planning experience</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac nobr">Personal characteristics:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to successfully navigate in a complex environment</li>
	<li>Strong leadership ability</li>
	<li>Ability to communicate crisply and candidly</li>
	<li>Results oriented, proven high level of performance</li>
	<li>Ability to manage tight deadlines, organize, and prioritize work independently</li>
	<li>Flexibility in exploring a variety of business areas</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("training", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">Associates will participate in a formal education and orientation programs to learn more about Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America business, culture and values, as well as to network with executives and other college hires. Additionally, interns will participate in various networking and learning opportunities throughout the duration of the summer.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<% call expandableH2("locations", false) %>
<div>
<p class="bac">The internship program will take place primarily in Charlotte, NC and Wilmington, DE; but we do require geographic flexibility from our full time program participants.</p>
</div></div>

